          <num>12-112</num>
          <heading>Limit of time for appeals</heading>
          <content>
            <p>Sec. 12-112. Limit of time for appeals.No appeal from the doings of the assessors in any town shall be heard or entertained by the board of assessment appeals unless referred to it at one of its meetings during the month of September in the case of an appeal related to motor vehicle assessment or unless written appeal is made on or before February twentieth in accordance with the provisions of section12-111.
